                        sling:resourceType="gotomarket/components/content/richtext"
                        text="&lt;p>&lt;b>From September 2017, Postbank will offer its customers the option to pay with their smartphones using NFC technology. The bank is one of the first on the German market to introduce Visa credit card payments based on Host Card Emulation (HCE) technology. Postbank will use the mobile payment solution created by equensWorldline. Postbank customers will soon be able to pay with their Android smartphones at all Visa contactless terminals.&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>Wolf Kunisch, COO and Deputy CEO at equensWorldline: &amp;quot;We have had a trusting business relationship with Postbank since 1998 and have successfully implemented several projects since then. We are delighted to now support Postbank with our NFC solution for Android smartphones. When it comes to payments, end customers are calling for new, mobile and intuitive solutions. With the equensWorldline mobile payment platform, Postbank is now offering its customers an innovative solution for card-based payment transactions.&amp;quot;&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>Read the full&amp;nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;press release NFC mobile payments&quot; href=&quot;/content/worldline/en/press-releases-general/2017/pr-2017_09_22_01.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>press release&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;on the Worldline website&lt;/p>&#xa;"
